Package org.drasyl.pipeline

Class AbstractPipeline

java.lang.Object
org.drasyl.pipeline.AbstractPipeline
All Implemented Interfaces:
Pipeline
Direct Known Subclasses:
DrasylPipeline, EmbeddedPipeline
public abstract class AbstractPipeline extends Object implements Pipeline
Abstract Pipeline implementation, that needs head and tail.

    • isWritable

      public boolean isWritable()
      Description copied from interface: Pipeline
      Returns true if the pipeline accepts new outbound messages for processing. Any calls to Pipeline.processOutbound(Address, Object) while this method returns false will be rejected with an exceptionally future.
      Specified by:
      isWritable in interface Pipeline

    • messagesBeforeUnwritable

      public int messagesBeforeUnwritable()
      Description copied from interface: Pipeline
      Returns the remaining number of messages the pipeline will accept for processing before Pipeline.isWritable() returns false. This quantity will always be non-negative. If Pipeline.isWritable() is false then 0 will be returned.
      Specified by:
      messagesBeforeUnwritable in interface Pipeline
